<div id="review_3434572432" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3434572432" />
    <a title="Redfox5" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3816075-redfox5"><img alt="Redfox5" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1512680087p2/3816075.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3434572432?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Redfox5" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Redfox5" href="/user/show/3816075-redfox5">Redfox5</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780192806352" href="/book/show/3077124-persian-letters">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3816075-redfox5?shelf=iran">iran</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3816075-redfox5?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3816075-redfox5?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3816075-redfox5?shelf=france">france</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3434572432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7877418347226716993">For a classic, this ain&apos;t half bad. It&apos;s more readable than some of them tend to be and it&apos;s pretty interesting at times.<br/><br/>It&apos;s letters between a Muslim man from Persia (Iran- which I now know as it was a question on our family quiz night) who is travelling in France. It includes his observations on weston culture and his own.<br/><br/>We also get a bit of drama from the harem, although not as much as I would have liked, it does ramp up a bit towards the end though.<br/><br/>Like I said, this wasn&apos;t bad but it didn&apos;t</span>
  <span id="freeText7877418347226716993" style="display:none">For a classic, this ain't half bad. It's more readable than some of them tend to be and it's pretty interesting at times.<br /><br />It's letters between a Muslim man from Persia (Iran- which I now know as it was a question on our family quiz night) who is travelling in France. It includes his observations on weston culture and his own.<br /><br />We also get a bit of drama from the harem, although not as much as I would have liked, it does ramp up a bit towards the end though.<br /><br />Like I said, this wasn't bad but it didn't pull me in completely, only for short bursts at a time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7877418347226716993" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
