<div id="review_402759440" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/402759440" />
    <a title="Ezri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12312848-ezri"><img alt="Ezri" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/images/nophoto/user/c_111x148.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/402759440?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ezri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ezri" href="/user/show/12312848-ezri">Ezri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12312848-ezri?shelf=required-reading">required-reading</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer402759440" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1404331208945077487">A strangely contemporary post-ironic skewering of Western civilization; something like the Team America of its time. While it ruthlessly mocks Parisian culture, it ultimately vindicates it using hateful and ignorant stereotypes of those who stand outside it. And also much like Team America, it is wildly and spitefully entertaining.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


