<div id="review_1925993986" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1925993986" />
    <a title="Garrett" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16476611-garrett"><img alt="Garrett" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491774191p2/16476611.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1925993986?book_show_action=true">Mar 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Garrett" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Garrett" href="/user/show/16476611-garrett">Garrett</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1925993986" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4234664092711034473">This book utilizes very interesting narrative techniques; deciding to tell the story through a series of letters between travelers. Reading the Persian Letters is a lot like panning for gold. You have to dig through quite a bit of dull dirt to get to the interesting gold nuggets.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


